      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 430: This removes the previous coalescing for momentary hook buttons and now forwards both edges as absolute state changes. A quick 0-\u003e1-\u003e0 press used to produce one logical hook intent; now the release edge can be interpreted as `HangUp` if the call becomes active before it is processed, causing an answered call to be dropped immediately on devices that report hook as a momentary pulse. Please preserve pulse coalescing for short transitions while still handling true absolute on-hook/off-hook changes.\n```suggestion\n                const auto now \u003d std::chrono::steady_clock::now();\n                if (!hook \u0026\u0026 now - ctx.lastHookEvent \u003c std::chrono::milliseconds(300))\n                    return;\n                ctx.lastHookEvent \u003d now;\n                qCDebug(LOG_CALLCTL) \u003c\u003c \"hook switch changed, offHook\u003d\" \u003c\u003c hook;\n                Q_EMIT parent_.hookSwitchChanged(hook);\n```",
